    "creation_date" : 1312454638,
    "answer_id" : 6940001,
    "question_id" : 957700,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Except the way described in the approved answer, there's another way if you have single native libs in your project.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>in Project properties->Java Build Path->Tab \"Source\" there's a list of your source-folders</li>\n<li>For each entry, there's \"Native library locations\", which also supports paths within the workspace.</li>\n<li>This will make Eclipse add it to your <code>java.library.path</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
