    "question_id" : 957700,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I think there is another reason for wanting to set <code>java.library.path</code>. Subversion comes with many libraries and Eclipse won't see these unless <code>java.library.path</code> can be appended. For example I'm on OS-X, so the libraries are under <code>\\opt\\subversion\\lib</code>. There are a lot of them and I'd like to keep them where they are (not copy them into a standard lib directory).</p>\n\n<p>Project settings won't fix this.</p>\n"
  }, {
